'''吉诺卡斯特'''（{{lang-sq|Gjirokastër}}）位于[[阿尔巴尼亚|阿尔巴尼亚]]南部，是[[吉诺卡斯特州|吉诺卡斯特州]]的首府，全市人口约25,301人（2011年），吉諾卡斯特素有“'''石头城'''”的美誉。

吉诺卡斯特古城是[[世界文化遺產|世界文化遺產]]之一，于2005年入选，因为它是保护完好的[[奥斯曼土耳其帝国|奥斯曼土耳其帝国]]城镇，始建于公元四世纪。

它也是[[阿尔巴尼亚劳动党|阿尔巴尼亚劳动党]]领导人[[恩維爾·霍查|恩維爾·霍查]]和作家[[伊斯梅尔·卡达莱|伊斯梅尔·卡达莱]]的故乡。还是革命电影《[[宁死不屈|宁死不屈]]》的故事发生的地方和拍摄地点。

吉诺卡斯特是阿尔巴尼亚南部的商业中心，有公路通往发罗拉港，近郊产[[褐煤|褐煤]]。有机械制造、木材加工、烟草、皮革、纺织和食品等工业。有中世纪城堡、清真寺、教堂和博物馆、游览地。

==歷史==
===古代===
考古證據指出，在[[青銅時代|青銅時代]]這個地區居住著可能會說[[希臘語|希臘西北部方言]]的人群。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hammond|first1=Nicholas Geoffrey Lemprière|title=Migrations and Invasions in Greece and Adjacent Areas|date=1976|publisher=Noyes Press|isbn=9780815550471|pages=153|url=https://books.google.gr/books?hl=el&id=O9saAAAAYAAJ&dq=|quote=南部巴爾克地區古墓葬的連接與[[庫克斯|庫克斯]]或Mati tumuli不同，但與Vajze和南阿爾巴尼亞的古墓葬相近。例如，在長青銅色的針腳，滾頂針，雙容器中。 手柄由一個橫桿分開，以及一個早期類型的小眼鏡腓骨。 此外，巴爾克典型的'西北幾何風格'的陶器現在不在北部，而是在阿爾巴尼亞的中部和南部以及此時的約阿尼納平原。 Shkumbi山谷南部和Ochrid湖的人們很可能會講西北希臘語，當移民將許多親屬帶入希臘半島時留下的殘留物。|access-date=2018-04-30|archive-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609171256/https://books.google.gr/books?hl=el&id=O9saAAAAYAAJ&dq=|dead-url=no}}</ref>考古學家在Gjirokastër發現了早期[[鐵器時代|鐵器時代]]的陶器物品，最早出現在Pazhok的青銅器時代[[艾巴申州|艾巴申州]]，並且遍及[[阿爾巴尼亞|阿爾巴尼亞]]。<ref name="Boardman1982">{{cite book|last=Boardman|first=John|title=The Prehistory of the Balkans and the Middle East and the Aegean World, Tenth to Eighth centuries B.C.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vXljf8JqmkoC&pg=PA223|accessdate=1 October 2010|date=1982-08-05|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-22496-3|location=Cambridge|page=223|archive-date=2014-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140709023036/http://books.google.com/books?id=vXljf8JqmkoC&pg=PA223|dead-url=no}}</ref>
Gjirokastër周圍地區最早的記錄居民是屬於[[Epirus|Epirote]]群[[Chaonians|Chaonians]]的[[古希臘語|希臘語]]部落。<ref>{{cite book|title=The Cambridge Ancient History: pt. 1. The prehistory of the Balkans; and the Middle East and the Aegean world, tenth to eighth centuries B.C|date=1982|publisher=Cambridge University Press|page=284|url=https://books.google.gr/books?hl=el&id=W43xAAAAMAAJ&dq=|language=en|quote=Inscriptional evidence of the Chaones is lacking until the Hellenistic period; but Ps.-Scylax, describing the situation of c. 580-560, put the southern limit of the Illyrians just north of the Chaones, which indicates that the Chaones did not speak Illyrian and the acceptance of the Chaones into the Epirote Alliance in the 330s suggests strongly that they were Greek-speaking}}</ref>

===中世紀===
[[File:Gjirokaster_2016_Albania_typical_street.jpg|thumb]]描繪了歷史悠久的城市中心。]]

城市的牆壁可追溯到公元三世紀。城堡的高石牆是從第六世紀到十二世紀建造的。<ref>{{cite book |title=Countries & Cultures of the World: The Pacific, Former Soviet Union, & Europe |last=Wilson |first=Wesley |year=1997 |publisher=Professional Press|location=Chapel Hill, N.C |oclc=1570873038 |page=149 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TWojAQAAIAAJ&q=City+of+Stone+gjirokaster&dq=City+of+Stone+gjirokaster&cd=4 |accessdate=13 June 2010}}</ref>在此期間，Gjirokastër發展成為一個主要的商業中心，被稱為'Argyropolis'（{{lang-grc |Ἀργυρόπολις}}，意為“銀城”）或'Argyrokastron'（{{lang-grc |Ἀργυρόκαστρον}}，意思是“銀城堡”）。<ref name="Dvornik">{{cite book | title=The Idea of Apostolicity in Byzantium and the Legend of the Apostle Andrew | url=https://archive.org/details/ideaofapostolici0000dvor | author=Dvornik, Francis | authorlink = Francis Dvornik | year=1958 | publisher=Harvard University Press | location=Cambridge | page=[https://archive.org/details/ideaofapostolici0000dvor/page/219 219] | oclc=1196640}}</ref>

這個城市是[[伊庇魯斯|伊庇魯斯]][[Despotate|Despotate]]的一部分，並於1336年首次由[[Argyrokastro|Argyrokastro]][[John_VI_Kantakouzenos|John VI Kantakouzenos]]提及。<ref name="Kiel">{{cite book|last=Kiel|first=Machiel|title=Ottoman Architecture in Albania, 1385–1912|url=https://books.google.com/books?ct=result&id=2xYzAAAAIAAJ&dq=%22The+city+is+first+mentioned+by+Cantacuzenos+in+1336%22&q=The+city+is+first+mentioned+by+Cantacuzenos+in+1336%C2%B0)+by+the+name+of+Argyrokastro#search_anchor|publisher=Research Centre for Islamic History, Art and Culture|accessdate=2 October 2010|isbn=978-92-9063-330-3|location=Beşiktaş, Istanbul|page=138|archive-date=2020-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314185039/https://books.google.com/books?ct=result&id=2xYzAAAAIAAJ&dq=%22The+city+is+first+mentioned+by+Cantacuzenos+in+1336%22&q=The+city+is+first+mentioned+by+Cantacuzenos+in+1336%C2%B0%29+by+the+name+of+Argyrokastro#search_anchor|dead-url=no}}</ref>第一次提到[[阿爾巴尼亞人|阿爾巴尼亞族]]游牧團體發生在14世紀初，他們在那裡尋找新的牧場和破壞該地區的定居點。<ref name="Giakoumissss"/> These Albanians had entered the region and took advantage of the situation after the [[Black_death|Black death]] had decimated the local Epirote population.<ref name="Giakoumissss">Giakoumis, Konstantinos (2003), [https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Kosta_Giakoumis/publication/233673710_Fourteenth-century_Albanian_migration_and_the_relative_autochthony_of_the_Albanians_in_Epeiros._The_case_of_Gjirokaster/links/0deec52ab0987b856e000000.pdf Fourteenth-century Albanian migration and the ‘relative autochthony’ of the Albanians in Epeiros. The case of Gjirokastër.] {{Wayback|url=https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Kosta_Giakoumis/publication/233673710_Fourteenth-century_Albanian_migration_and_the_relative_autochthony_of_the_Albanians_in_Epeiros._The_case_of_Gjirokaster/links/0deec52ab0987b856e000000.pdf |date=20150924135025 }}" ''Byzantine and Modern Greek Studies''. '''27'''. (1). p. 179: "The Albanians originating... According to the sources, there were two migrant groups, the one which travelled via Ohrid and ended in Thessaly while the other, moving through Kelcyre, reached Gjirokaster and the despotate. The purpose of their occupation was to search for new pasture lands. The combination of fertile plains and mountains rich in grasslands in the region of Gjirokaster was ideal for the poor nomadic Albanians who did not hesitate to ravage cities when they lacked provisions.."; p. 182. "Furthermore, I presented evidence that the in the fourteenth century immigrant Albanians taking advantage of the decimation of the local Epirote population by to the Black death also migrated into the regions of Gjirokastër."</ref>在1386年至1417年期間，它在[[伊庇魯斯的統治者|伊庇魯斯的統治者]]和阿爾巴尼亞[[約翰澤內維西|約翰澤內維西]]的氏族之間有爭議。<ref name=Marandet>{{cite book|last1=Marandet|first1=Marie-Claude|title=La ville et le plat pays|date=2017|publisher=Presses universitaires de Perpignan|isbn=9782354122881|page=175, 181|url=https://books.google.gr/books?id=Nj87DwAAQBAJ&dq=|language=fr}}</ref>在1399年，該城市的希臘居民加入了伊庇魯斯的暴君[[Esau_de'Buondelmonti|Esau]]組織，以對抗阿爾巴尼亞族和[[阿蒙羅族|阿蒙羅族]]的部落成員。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Hammond|first1=Nicholas Geoffrey Lemprière|title=Migrations and Invasions in Greece and Adjacent Areas|date=1976|publisher=Noyes Press|isbn=9780815550471|page=61|url=https://books.google.gr/books?hl=el&id=O9saAAAAYAAJ&dq=|language=en|quote=There the Greek pocket of resistance, which preserved the Greek language even when its ruler was Serb or Italian, was the plateau of Ioannina and its hinterland... When Isaou, the Italian ruler of Ioannina, passed to the offensive in 1399, he had already won over the Mazarakii (Albanians) and the Malakasaei (perhaps Vlach- speakers) and he recruited Greeks evidently from Zagori, Papingo (above Konitsa), and "Druinoupolis with Argyrokastro and the great Zagoria" (probably the high country northwest of Argyrokastro, of which a part is still called Zagorie).|access-date=2018-04-30|archive-date=2020-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609171256/https://books.google.gr/books?hl=el&id=O9saAAAAYAAJ&dq=|dead-url=no}}</ref>在1417年它成為奧斯曼帝國的一部分，並於1419年成為[[阿爾巴尼亞Sanjak|阿爾巴尼亞Sanjak]][[縣城|縣城]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0009/000929/092980eo.pdf |title=Ethnographic and open-air museums |last1=Riza |first1=Emin |last2= |first2= |year=1992 |work= |publisher=UNESCO, Paris |accessdate=March 18, 2011 |archive-date=2018-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928182224/http://unesdoc.unesco.org/images/0009/000929/092980eo.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>在[[阿爾巴尼亞1432-36年的起義|阿爾巴尼亞1432-36年的起義]]期間，它被[[托皮亞·齊內維西|托皮亞·齊內維西]]下的部隊包圍，但反叛分子被[[圖拉漢貝|圖拉漢貝]]領導的鄂圖曼軍隊擊敗。<ref>{{cite book|last=Imber|first=Colin|title=The Crusade of Varna, 1443–45|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xeuaoghuq3cC|accessdate=31 July 2012|year=2006|publisher=Ashgate Publishing, Ltd.|isbn=9780754601449|page=27|archive-date=2020-10-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201030150237/https://books.google.com/books?id=xeuaoghuq3cC|dead-url=no}}</ref>在十七世紀七十年代，當地貴族[[曼托斯帕帕吉尼斯|曼托斯帕帕吉尼斯]]和帕諾斯凱斯托利科斯與[[神聖同盟（1571）|神聖同盟]]負責人討論了''作為希臘和阿爾巴尼亞被奴役的希臘代表''，[[約翰奧地利|約翰奧地利]]和其他各種歐洲統治者，反鄂圖曼帝國武裝鬥爭的可能性，但這一舉措毫無結果。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Vakalopoulos|first1=Apostolos Euangelou|title=History of Macedonia, 1354–1833|date=1973|publisher=Institute for Balkan Studies|page=195|url=https://books.google.gr/books?id=yOcJAQAAIAAJ&q=kestolikos&dq=kestolikos&hl=el&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiDvJ_Z_6fLAhULtRQKHf6cAtUQ6AEIHDAA|quote=The endeavours of two Epirote Greeks, Matthew (or Manthos) Papayiannis and Panos Kestolnikos, are worthy of mention at this point. As "Greek representatives of enslaved Greece and Albania", they came to an understanding with Don John of Austria..|access-date=2018-04-30|archive-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928213434/https://books.google.gr/books?id=yOcJAQAAIAAJ&q=kestolikos&dq=kestolikos&hl=el&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiDvJ_Z_6fLAhULtRQKHf6cAtUQ6AEIHDAA|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Chasiotis, 1965, p. 241: "embajadores griegos de la baja Grecia y Alvania"</ref><ref name=Cini>{{cite book|last1=Cini|first1=Giorgio|title=Il Mediterraneo Nella Seconda Metà Del '500 Alla Luce Di Lepanto|date=1974|publisher=Leo S. Olschki|page=238|url=https://books.google.gr/books?id=70FoAAAAMAAJ&q=Delusi+rimasero+pure+i+ribelli+dell%27Epiro+del+Nord,+dove+si+erano+sollevati+i+notabili+greci+di+Argirocastron+Manthos+Papagiannis+e+Panos+Kestolicos.+Questi+notabili+si+erano+accor-+dati+con+l%27arcivescovo+di+Ochrida+Ioachim+ed+anche+con+alcuni&dq=Delusi+rimasero+pure+i+ribelli+dell%27Epiro+del+Nord,+dove+si+erano+sollevati+i+notabili+greci+di+Argirocastron+Manthos+Papagiannis+e+Panos+Kestolicos.+Questi+notabili+si+erano+accor-+dati+con+l%27arcivescovo+di+Ochrida+Ioachim+ed+anche+con+alcuni&hl=el&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjX0ILF6b_MAhWsKsAKHcEmBg0Q6AEIHTAA|language=it|quote=Delusi rimasero pure i ribelli dell'Epiro del Nord, dove si erano sollevati i notabili greci di Argirocastron Manthos Papagiannis e Panos Kestolicos. Questi notabili si erano accordati con l'arcivescovo di Ochrida Ioachim ed anche con alcuni metropolis della Macedonia occidentale e dell'Epiro, si erano assicurati promesse di Don Juan per un sostegno armato... [Disappointed were also the rebels of Northern Epirus, where they had raised the Greek notables of Argirocastron Manthos Papagiannis and Panos Kestolicos. These chiefs had agreed with the Archbishop of Ochrida Ioachim and also with some metropolitans of western Macedonia and Epirus, and had secured promises of Don Juan for armed support...]|access-date=2018-04-30|archive-date=2018-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180928214802/https://books.google.gr/books?id=70FoAAAAMAAJ&q=Delusi+rimasero+pure+i+ribelli+dell%27Epiro+del+Nord,+dove+si+erano+sollevati+i+notabili+greci+di+Argirocastron+Manthos+Papagiannis+e+Panos+Kestolicos.+Questi+notabili+si+erano+accor-+dati+con+l%27arcivescovo+di+Ochrida+Ioachim+ed+anche+con+alcuni&dq=Delusi+rimasero+pure+i+ribelli+dell%27Epiro+del+Nord,+dove+si+erano+sollevati+i+notabili+greci+di+Argirocastron+Manthos+Papagiannis+e+Panos+Kestolicos.+Questi+notabili+si+erano+accor-+dati+con+l%27arcivescovo+di+Ochrida+Ioachim+ed+anche+con+alcuni&hl=el&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjX0ILF6b_MAhWsKsAKHcEmBg0Q6AEIHTAA|dead-url=no}}</ref>

根據1670年訪問該城市的[[土耳其人|土耳其人]]旅行者，當時在城堡內有200間房屋，在'KyçykVarosh'基督教東部社區有200間房屋 意思是城堡外面的小鄰居），'Byjyk Varosh'（意思是城堡外的大街區）有150個房屋，還有另外6個社區：Palorto、Vutosh、Dunavat、Manalat、Haxhi Bey及Memi Bey，城堡周圍的山丘。<ref name="Elsie trnaslates Celebi">{{cite journal | url=http://www.elsie.de/pdf/articles/A2007CelebiGjirokastraAlbanica.pdf | title=GJIROKASTRA nga udhëpërshkrimi i Evlija Çelebiut | author=Elsie, Robert | journal=Albanica ekskluzive | date=March 2007 | issue=66 | pages=73–76 | access-date=2018-04-30 | archive-date=2019-12-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222004546/http://www.elsie.de/pdf/articles/A2007CelebiGjirokastraAlbanica.pdf | dead-url=no }}</ref>據旅行者說，當時該市有大約2000座房屋，8座清真寺，3座教堂，280間商店，5個噴泉和5個旅館。<ref name="Elsie trnaslates Celebi"/>從十六世紀到十九世紀初，吉諾卡斯特從一個主要的基督教城市變成了一個擁有大多數穆斯林教徒的城市，這是由於大部分城市人口皈依[[伊斯蘭教|伊斯蘭教]]以及來自周邊農村的[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]皈依者。<ref name="Giakoumis">Giakoumis, Konstantinos (2010). "[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=aCdYHU9PtiIC&pg=PA86&dq=Gjirokast%C3%ABr+Muslims&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false The Orthodox Church in Albania Under the Ottoman Rule 15th–19th Century] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=aCdYHU9PtiIC&pg=PA86&dq=Gjirokast%C3%ABr+Muslims&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20180101030009 }}". In Schmitt, Oliver Jens & Andreas Rathberger (eds). ''Religion und Kultur im albanischsprachigen Südosteuropa [Religion and culture in Albanian-speaking southeastern Europe]]''. Peter Lang. pp. 86–87.</ref><ref name="Kokolakis"/>

===現代===
[[File:AutonomyDeclaration1914.jpg|right]]的官員[[北方埃比羅獨立宣言|北方埃比羅獨立宣言]] 1914年3月1日。在背景中看到的河[[Drin（river）|Drin]]。]]

1811年，吉諾卡斯特成為了[[阿尼娜的Pashalik|阿尼娜的Pashalik]]的一部分，然後由阿爾巴尼亞出生的[[約阿尼納的阿里帕夏|約阿尼納的阿里帕夏]]領導，並在1822年被改造成巴爾幹半島西南部的一個半自治的地方，直到他去世為止。1868年被帕夏克人淪陷後，這座城市是埃爾吉里[[sanjak|sanjak]]的首府。 1880年7月23日，阿爾巴尼亞南部[普里茲倫聯盟]委員會在該市舉行了一次大會，決定如果鄂圖曼帝國的阿爾巴尼亞人口居住區被割讓給鄰國，他們就會起而反抗。<ref name="Gawrych2006">{{cite book|last=Gawrych|first=George Walter|title=The Crescent and the Eagle: Ottoman Rule, Islam and the Albanians, 1874–1913|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wPOtzk-unJgC&pg=PA23|accessdate=30 September 2010|year=2006|publisher=I.B. Tauris|isbn=978-1-84511-287-5|location=London|pages=23–64}}</ref>在[[阿爾巴尼亞民族覺醒運動|阿爾巴尼亞民族覺醒運動]]（1831-1912）期間，該城市是該運動的主要中心，據報這一時期該城市的一些團體設立阿爾巴尼亞民族英雄[[斯坎德培|斯坎德培]]的肖像。<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite book|last=Gawrych|first=George Walter|title=The Crescent and the Eagle: Ottoman Rule, Islam and the Albanians, 1874–1913|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wPOtzk-unJgC&pg=PA23#v=onepage&q=Ergiri%20proved%20a%20major%20center%20of%20Albanian%20national%20activity&f=false|accessdate=30 September 2010|year=2006|publisher=I.B. Tauris|isbn=978-1-84511-287-5|location=London|pages=148}}</ref>從十九世紀中期開始吉諾卡斯特也通過擔任“卡迪”（公務員）並且是伊斯蘭文化的重要中心的個人對更廣泛的奧斯曼帝國作出了顯著貢獻。<ref name="Çaksu">Ali, Çaksu (2006). ''[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=smhpAAAAMAAJ&q=Ergiri&dq=Ergiri&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y Proceedings of the Second International Symposium on Islamic Civilisation in the Balkans, Tirana, Albania, 4–7 December 2003] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=smhpAAAAMAAJ&q=Ergiri&dq=Ergiri&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y |date=20181003115338 }}''. Research Center for Islamic History, Art and Culture. p. 115. "At least since the middle of the nineteenth century; families or individuals from Gjirokastër (the Ottoman Ergiri or Ergiri Kasrı) in Southern Albania, and from Libohova, a small town located twenty kilometers from Gjirokastër, gave a huge number of Kadıs, who were in charge in the whole Ottoman Empire, making of these two localities important centres of Islamic culture."</ref>1909 - 1912年這座城市的親阿爾巴尼亞族分裂為兩個群體：希望與希臘人合作的城市自由派和在鄉下組織游擊隊的阿族[[民族主義|民族主義]]者。<ref name="Kokolakis"/> 在十九世紀和二十世紀初，說阿爾巴尼亞語的穆斯林是吉諾卡斯特的主要居民，而只有少數說希臘語的家庭居住在那裡。<ref name="Kokolakis">Kokolakis, Mihalis (2003). [http://helios-eie.ekt.gr/EIE/bitstream/10442/8080/1/N01.074.0.pdf {{Wayback|url=http://helios-eie.ekt.gr/EIE/bitstream/10442/8080/1/N01.074.0.pdf |date=20170201125340 }} ''Το ύστερο Γιαννιώτικο Πασαλίκι: χώρος, διοίκηση και πληθυσμός στην τουρκοκρατούμενη Ηπειρο (1820–1913) [The late Pashalik of Ioannina: Space, administration and population in Ottoman ruled Epirus (1820–1913)]''. EIE-ΚΝΕ. p.52. "β. Ο διεσπαρμένος ελληνόφωνος πληθυσμός περιλάμβανε... και μικρό αριθμό οικογενειών στα αστικά κέντρα του Αργυροκάστρου και της Αυλώνας. [b. The scattered Greek-speaking population included ... and a small number of families in the cities of Gjirokastra and Vlora.]"; p. 54. "Η μουσουλμανική κοινότητα της Ηπείρου, με εξαίρεση τους μικρούς αστικούς πληθυσμούς των νότιων ελληνόφωνων περιοχών, τους οποίους προαναφέραμε, και τις δύο με τρεις χιλιάδες διεσπαρμένους «Τουρκόγυφτους», απαρτιζόταν ολοκληρωτικά από αλβανόφωνους, και στα τέλη της Τουρκοκρατίας κάλυπτε τα 3/4 περίπου του πληθυσμού των αλβανόφωνων περιοχών και περισσότερο από το 40% του συνόλου. [The Muslim community in Epirus, with the exception of small urban populations of the southern Greek-speaking areas, which we mentioned, and 2-3000 dispersed "Muslim Romani", consisted entirely of Albanian speakers, and in the late Ottoman period covered approximately 3/4 of population ethnic Albanian speaking areas and more than 40% of the total area."; pp.55–56. "Σ' αυτά τα μέρη οι μουσουλμανικές κοινότητες, όταν υπήρχαν, περιορίζονταν στο συμπαγή πληθυσμό ορισμένων πόλεων και κωμοπόλεων (Αργυρόκαστρο, Λιμπόχοβο, Λεσκοβίκι, Δέλβινο, Παραμυθιά). [In these parts of the Muslim communities, where present, were limited to compact population of certain towns and cities (Gjirokastra, Libohovë, Leskovik, Delvino, Paramythia)." p. 91. Στο Αργυρόκαστρο οι Αλβανιστές διασπάστηκαν ανάμεσα στους φιλελεύθερους της πόλης, που ζητούσαν τη συνεργασία με τους Έλληνες, και στα ακραία εθνικιστικά στοιχεία, που σχημάτισαν στην ύπαιθρο ανταρτικές ομάδες. [The Albanians of Gjirokastër were split between the liberals of the city, calling for cooperation with the Greeks, and the extreme nationalist elements, which formed in the countryside as guerrilla groups.]"; pp. 370, 374.</ref>

考慮到其龐大的希臘人口，這座城市在1912年至1913年的[[第一次巴爾幹戰爭|第一次巴爾幹戰爭]]期間被希臘人宣布和占領，隨後鄂圖曼土耳其人從該地區撤退。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.da.mod.uk/search?SearchableText=greek+minority+in+Albania|title=The Greek Minority in Albania in the Aftermath of Communism|author=James Pettifer|publisher=Conflict Studies Research Centre, Royal Military Academy Sandhurst|format=PDF|location=Camberley, Surrey|page=4|accessdate=20 December 2010|archive-date=2016-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160323074225/http://www.da.mod.uk/search?searchabletext=greek+minority+in+albania|dead-url=yes}}</ref>但是，根據1913年[[倫敦條約|倫敦條約]]和[[佛羅倫薩北部伊庇魯斯自治共和國議定書|佛羅倫薩議定書]]12月17日的條款，該項目被授予阿爾巴尼亞1913年獨立。<ref>{{cite book|first=Dimitri|last= Pentzopoulos|title=The Balkan Exchange of Minorities and Its Impact on Greece|page=28|publisher= C. Hurst & Co|year=2002|isbn=1-85065-674-6|location=London}}</ref>

這一事件證明，當地希臘人民非常不受歡迎，他們在[[Georgios_Christakis-Zografos|Georgios Christakis-Zografos]]下的代表在吉諾卡斯特組成了Panepirotic議會，抗議希臘人留在吉諾卡斯特生活。<ref>{{cite book|first1=Valeria|last1= Heuberger|first2=Arnold|last2= Suppan|first3= Elisabeth|last3= Vyslonzil |title=Brennpunkt Osteuropa: Minderheiten im Kreuzfeuer des Nationalismus |year=1996| publisher=Oldenbourg Wissenschaftsverlag |language=de |page= 68 |location=Vienna |isbn=978-3-486-56182-1 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=edAu3dxEwwgC&q=nordepirus#v=onepage&q=panepirotische%20versammlung&f=false}}</ref>大會與希臘合併之後，要求大國的部隊對吉諾卡斯特，[[薩蘭達|薩蘭達]]和[[科爾察|科爾察]]的地區實行地方自治或國際佔領。<ref>{{cite book|last=Ference|first= Gregory Curtis|url=https://books.google.com/books?ct=result&id=RSLsAAAAMAAJ&dq=panepirotic%2Bassembly&q=%22meets+in+Gjirokaster%2C+where+it+announces+that%2C+short+of+incorporation+with+Greece%2C+it+demands+either+local+autonomy+or+an+international+occupation+of+Great+Power+forces+for+the+districts+of+Gjirokaster+and+Korçë.%22#search_anchor|title=Chronology of 20th-Century Eastern European History|publisher= Gale Research|year=1994|isbn= 978-0-8103-8879-6|page= 9}}</ref>

[[File:Hodza_house.jpg|220px]]的房子，他長大的地方。]]

1914年3月，吉諾卡斯特宣布了[[北方Epirote獨立宣言|北方Epirote獨立宣言]]，並在[[科孚協議|科孚協議]]中得到確認。<ref>{{cite book | last = Winnifrith | first = Tom | title = Badlands-Borderland: A History of Southern Albania/Northern Epirus | publisher = Duckworth | year = 2002 | location = London | page = 130 | isbn = 0-7156-3201-9}}</ref>然而，共和國卻很短暫，因為阿爾巴尼亞在[[第一次世界大戰|第一次世界大戰]]開始時就崩潰了。<ref>{{cite book|url= http://www.p-ng.si/~vanesa/doktorati/interkulturni/3GregoricBon.pdf|title= Contested Spaces and Negotiated Identities in Dhermi/Drimades of Himare/Himara area, Southern Albania|first= Nataša Gregorič|last= Bon|publisher= Nova Gorica|year= 2008|page= 140|chapter= Formation of the Albanian Nation-State and the Protocol of Corfu (1914)|format= PDF|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110610025500/http://www.p-ng.si/~vanesa/doktorati/interkulturni/3GregoricBon.pdf|archivedate= 2011-06-10|df= |access-date= 2018-04-30}}</ref>希臘軍隊於1914年10月至11月返回，並再次與薩蘭達和[[科爾察|科爾察]]一起佔領了吉諾卡斯特。<ref name="Konidaris">{{cite book |last1=Konidaris |first1=Gerasimos |authorlink1=  |editor1-first=Stephanie |editor1-last=Schwandner-Sievers |title=The new Albanian migrations |url=https://books.google.com/?id=05Mw4-b9oN0C&pg=PA74&dq=omonoia+five#v=onepage&q&f=false |year=2005 |publisher=Sussex Academic Publishing |isbn= 9781903900789 |page=65 }}</ref>1916年4月，希臘人稱為[[北方伊庇魯斯|北方伊庇魯斯]]的領土，包括吉諾卡斯特，被併入希臘。<ref name="Konidaris"/> [[巴黎和會|巴黎和會]]簽署後恢復了戰前的狀況，基本上維持了1913年佛羅倫薩議定書中確定的邊界線，該城市又被歸還到阿爾巴尼亞人的控制之下。<ref>{{cite book|first1=Vassilis|last1= Nitsiakos|first2= Constantinos|last2= Mantzos|chapter=Negotiating Culture: Political Uses of Polyphonic Folk Songs in Greece and Albania|page= 197|title=Greece and the Balkans: Identities, Perceptions and Cultural Encounters|editor1-first= Demetres|editor1-last=Tziovas|publisher= Ashgate Publishing|year=2003|isbn= 0-7546-0998-7|location=Aldershot, England}}</ref>

隨著城市在[[阿爾巴尼亞公國|阿爾巴尼亞公國]]的納入，希臘人被剝奪了少數人的權利。
儘管如此，吉諾卡斯特作為一個多民族城市仍然保留著希臘文字。<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Manta|first1=Eleftheria|title=Aspects of the Italian Influence upon Greek - Albanian Relations during the Interwar Period|journal=didaktorika.gr|date=2005|page=30|doi=10.12681/eadd/23718|url=https://www.didaktorika.gr/eadd/handle/10442/23718|accessdate=27 June 2017|publisher=University of Thessaloniki|language=el|archive-date=2018-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812021627/https://www.didaktorika.gr/eadd/handle/10442/23718|dead-url=no}}</ref>
1939年4月，在[[意大利入侵阿爾巴尼亞|意大利入侵阿爾巴尼亞]]之後，吉諾卡斯特被[意大利]佔領。1940年12月8日，[[希臘戰爭|希臘戰爭]]期間，希臘軍隊進入城市並停留了五個月，隨後於1941年4月向[[納粹德國|納粹德國]]投降，並將該城重新歸為意大利司令部。1943年9月意大利在[[卡西比爾停戰|卡西比爾停戰]]投降後，該城被德軍佔領，並於1944年最終返回[[解放日（阿爾巴尼亞）|阿爾巴尼亞控制]]。

戰後的共產主義政權將這個城市發展成為工業和商業中心。它被提升到博物館城市的地位，<ref name="Petersen"/> 因為它是[[阿爾巴尼亞人民社會主義共和國|阿爾巴尼亞人民社會主義共和國]]領導人的誕生地，[[恩維爾·霍查|恩維爾·霍查]]，他於1908年出生在那裡。他的房子被改建成博物館。<ref name="Murati">{{cite news|url=http://www.standard.al/index.php/kulture/9952.html |title=Tourism with the Dictator |last=Murati |first=Violeta |work=Standard |language=sq |accessdate=19 August 2010 }}{{dead link|date=May 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

1991年8月當地希臘社區成員拆除了吉諾卡斯特的威權領導人[[恩維爾·霍查|恩維爾·霍查]]的巨大雕像標誌著一黨制國家的結束。<ref>{{cite book|last1=Pettifer|first1=James|last2=Poulton|first2=Hugh|title=The Southern Balkans|date=1994|publisher=Minority Rights Group International|location=London|isbn=9781897693759|page=29|url=https://books.google.gr/books?hl=el&id=4Fy2AAAAIAAJ&dq="|quote=Under communism the Greek minority was subject to serious human rights abuses, particularly in terms of religious freedom, education in the Greek language and freedom of publication. It played a leading part in the struggle to end the one party state, with the demolition of the monumental statue of Enver Hoxha in Gjirokastra in August 1991 an important landmark}}</ref>1991年共產主義政權統治結束後，吉諾卡斯特遭受了嚴重的經濟問題。1993年春季，吉諾卡斯特爾地區成為希臘少數民族成員和阿爾巴尼亞警察之間衝突的中心。<ref name=Petiffer>{{cite book | last = Petiffer | first = James | title = The Greek Minority in Albania – In the Aftermath of Communism | publisher = Conflict Studies Research Centre | year = 2001 | location = Surrey, UK | ref = Petiffer01 | isbn = 1-903584-35-3 | url = http://kms1.isn.ethz.ch/serviceengine/Files/ISN/38652/ipublicationdocument_singledocument/5494CBC6-4F56-4EFD-B6DB-7FB1EC46CC11/en/2001_Jul_2.pdf | page = 13 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110706231739/http://kms1.isn.ethz.ch/serviceengine/Files/ISN/38652/ipublicationdocument_singledocument/5494CBC6-4F56-4EFD-B6DB-7FB1EC46CC11/en/2001_Jul_2.pdf | archivedate = 2011-07-06 | df =  | access-date = 2018-04-30 }}</ref>吉諾卡斯特特別受到[[1997年阿爾巴尼亞危機戰爭|1997年阿爾巴尼亞危機戰爭]]的大規模[[非法傳銷|非法傳銷]]計劃崩潰影響，這使整個[[阿爾巴尼亞經濟|阿爾巴尼亞經濟]]不穩定。<ref name="Jeffires"/> 這座城市成為反對[[薩利．貝里沙|薩利．貝里沙]]政府叛亂的焦點，暴力反政府抗議活動發生，最終迫使貝里沙辭職下台。1997年12月16日，霍查的故居被不明身份的襲擊者破壞，但後來又恢復原狀。<ref name="Lajmi22March">{{cite news|url=http://www.gazetalajmi.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=387:turizem-me-simbolet-e-komunizmit&catid=106:reportazh&Itemid=438|title=Tourism with the Communist Symbols|last=Lajmi|date=22 March 2010|work=Gazeta Lajmi|language=sq|accessdate=19 August 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711080221/http://www.gazetalajmi.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=387:turizem-me-simbolet-e-komunizmit&catid=106:reportazh&Itemid=438|archive-date=2011-07-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
